{"normalized_assets_id": "nassets_8ee03d2a72d0926df2e7a82a", "problem_id": "prob_59be777020dd0083125f3413", "normalized_question_text": "As shown in the figure, in the known $\\triangle ABC$, proceed with the following steps: \n(1) With centers at B and C, respectively, draw arcs with radii longer than $\\frac{1}{2}BC$, intersecting at points M and N; \n(2) Draw line MN intersecting AB at D, and connect CD. If $AC = 5$ and $AB = 12$, what is the perimeter of $\\triangle ACD$?", "normalized_answer_text": "\\textbf{Solution:} From the construction, we have that $MN$ bisects $BC$ perpendicularly,\\\\\n$\\therefore DB=DC$,\\\\\n$\\therefore$ the perimeter of $\\triangle ACD = AC+AD+CD = AC+AD+BD = AC+AB = 5+12 = \\boxed{17}$", "question_unit_normalization_map": [], "answer_unit_normalization_map": [], "variable_aliases": [{"original": "As", "canonical": "As", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "in", "canonical": "in", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "the", "canonical": "the", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "ABC", "canonical": "ABC", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "with", "canonical": "with", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "With", "canonical": "With", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "at", "canonical": "at", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "B", "canonical": "B", "variable_type": "symbol"}, {"original": "and", "canonical": "and", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "C", "canonical": "C", "variable_type": "symbol"}, {"original": "draw", "canonical": "draw", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "arcs", "canonical": "arcs", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "than", "canonical": "than", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "frac", "canonical": "frac", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "BC", "canonical": "BC", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "M", "canonical": "M", "variable_type": "symbol"}, {"original": "N", "canonical": "N", "variable_type": "symbol"}, {"original": "Draw", "canonical": "Draw